social_posts.post_text: Cute little powder bath. Something new and something old for a little soul. 🫶🏻#karamillerinteriors

Huge thank you to everyone @coastal_living for featuring this very special project! So much heart and soul went into this home and there are many amazing people who took part in it. Thank you to the talented @julialynnphotography and @lindseyellisbeatty for working their magic at the shoot. To @stephhuntwrites who truly captured the essence of this home and family in the article. To my team, you are so loyal and give your all to our projects - I would be nowhere without you. @beauclowneyarchitects Beau, Kate and Ryan - you were an absolute delight to partner with. It is so very refreshing to work with architects who are this creatively invested in their projects. You always have my highest recommendation. Daly and Sawyer, the builders, for being so hands on and such a pleasure to work alongside. And to @teach.us.to.count.the.days and family, your beautiful hearts shine through every facet of this home. It certainly lives up to its name, “Brightside.” Thank you for taking me along for the adventure. 🥰I am forever grateful. We are now booking full service projects for the second half of 2023 in the Charleston area.

T minus 6 weeks until @minnowswim lands in this sweet little shop at @theroyalpoincianaplaza ! It will be located in The Current building, alongside @hillhouse and @laviestylehouse . We are very excited to be designing the space for them here and know you will just love it! 🐟🐟🐟

In addition to wishing you all Happy Holidays and Merry Christmas, I wanted to take a moment to thank you from the bottom of my heart for your support this year. I feel so grateful to have this creative community. It has helped me build my business and has connected me to so many amazing people I would have never had the chance to know otherwise. So thank you…for all your encouraging comments, messages and support! We have many exciting things in store for 2023 and I can’t wait to share them with you! 📸: by my talented and beautiful friend @lindseypotterphotography

Incredibly grateful to be featured in this months @southernhomemag ✨This was such a rewarding project that almost didn’t happen due to covid, but the clients pressed on and are so glad they did. So much gratitude to them for trusting us throughout the entire process remotely (and during a pandemic!), @southernhomemag for the beautiful feature, @lynnleeterry for embracing the project and @brantleyphoto for her hard work and talent. @maxwellbuilding did an outstanding job on the build and YRA Design on the architecture. I’m so thankful that I get to design homes for a living. I could not do this without my amazing team and vendors who help make it all happen.🙏

My heart is so full of gratitude for this month’s @coastal_living feature! Each and every issue is such a treat and I am over the moon to be a part of such a widely loved and celebrated publication. Huge thank you to my hard working team, our amazing and trusting clients, the lovely and talented @brantleyphoto, @sarahbraywest and everyone on the CL team who embraced this story! @jsthuston @preich @patriciashannon Thank you, thank you, thank you! 🥰 Architecture: @mpdesignarch Build: @baldwin_innovative
Every day moments I don’t want to forget.😌So grateful to be starting life here. We are far from finished, but it’s starting to come together.
